\subsection{\href{https://beta.lmfdb.org/knowledge/show/lf.swan_slopes}{Swan slopes}}
\begin{definition}\label{lf.swan_slopes}
\uses{lf.galois_invariants,lf.padic_field}
Let $L/K$ be an extension of \hyperref[lf.padic_field]{$p$-adic fields}.
The \textbf{Swan slopes} of $L/K$ are the same as the nonnegative upper ramification
breaks of $L/K$.  In the case where $L/K$ is a Galois extension the upper breaks
are defined in Chapter IV of Serre's <i>Local Fields</i>
\cite{doi:10.1007/978-1-4757-5673-9,MR:0554237}.
For the general case where $L/K$ is separable but not necessarily
Galois see the appendix to Deligne \cite{MR:0771673}.  The Swan
slopes can be obtained by subtracting 1 from each of the positive \hyperref[lf.galois_invariants]{Artin
slopes} of $L/K$.
\end{definition}
